{"word":"G839 - αὔριον - aúrion - ow'-ree-on - Morrow","sections":[{"paragraph":"<strong>மூல வார்த்தை / Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">αὔριον</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>எழுத்துமாற்றம் / Transliteration: </strong><span class=\"transliteration\">aúrion</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>ஒலிபெயர்ப்பு / Phonetic: </strong><span class=\"phonetic\">ow'-ree-on</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>சுருக்க விளக்கம் / Short Definition: </strong><span class=\"short-definition\">Morrow</span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"parts-of-speech\"><strong>இலக்கண சொல்வகை / Part(s) of speech: </strong>Adverb / வினையடை</span>"},{"paragraph":"நாளை, மறுநாள் - வினையடை"},{"paragraph":"tomorrow"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"original-in-english\"><strong>ஆங்கில மூலம் / Original in English: </strong>From a derivative of the same as <a href=\"#/G109 - ἀήρ - aḗr - ah-ayr'/109\">G109</a> (meaning a <i>breeze</i>, that is, the morning <i>air</i>); properly <i>fresh</i>, that is, (adverbially with ellipsis of <a href=\"#/G2250 - ἡμέρα - hēméra - hay-mer'-ah/2250\">G2250</a>) <i>tomorrow:</i> - (to-) morrow, next day.</span>"},{"paragraph":""}]}